  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Priyansh, fixed a bug today? Work wins feel great. How did it go?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Fixed a tricky one. Took all day, but it feels good. Exhausted now, though. Sleep was terrible. How was your day?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Fixed a tricky one — that’s a solid win. Exhausted after a sleepless night? I get that. How did you unwind before bed?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Just lay there staring at ceiling. Phone on silent. Even tried counting sheep. Ha! No luck. Ended up scrolling Twitter. Not my best bedtime routine. 😅"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Scrolling Twitter before bed — not the best habit, but I get it. What’s one thing that helps you relax after a tough day?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Listening to music, maybe. But only mellow stuff. Or a Bollywood song sometimes. Helps calm my head. Though I’m too wired most nights. Kabhi khushi kabhi gham? Not the best choice, though. 😅"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Kabhi Khushi Kabhi Gham is a mood — maybe not the calmest pick. Mellow songs are the way to go. What’s your go-to relaxing track?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Probably \"Bekhayali\" by Arijit Singh. It’s slow, emotional, and makes me feel like everything’s going to be okay. But honestly, most times I just fall asleep to YouTube white noise. Jio Saavn playlist is good, but my eyes are heavy. 😴"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Bekhayali is a perfect calm-down track — that emotional slow burn helps unwind the mind. White noise is a smart fallback when eyes are heavy. Any other songs you turn to when you’re feeling wired?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Arijjit’s \"Apna Bana Le\" sometimes. Or \"Channa Mereya\" — though that one makes me miss Punjab a bit. 😅 Most of the time, I just let the playlist shuffle. If it’s not too peppy, I’m good. But yeah, I should probably try more Hindi oldies. The slow ones, like \"Pyar Hua Ikrar Hua\"."
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Apna Bana Le and Channa Mereya both carry that quiet, reflective vibe — which explains the sudden nostalgia for Punjab! Slow oldies are a gold mine for winding down. Did you ever try Lata Mangeshkar’s ‘Mera Joota Paida’ for a real mood?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Nope, never heard that one. But I’ve heard of her — legend, right? Maybe I’ll look it up. Slow, classic songs are a good idea. I do like the old Hindi film music sometimes. It’s different from the stuff playing on the radio these days. Maybe I’ll give it a try tonight. Gotta sleep better somehow. 😅"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Absolutely — Lata Mangeshkar is a legend. Her songs carry that timeless calm no modern track can match. Old Hindi film music is a perfect bedtime escape. Will you give it a try tonight, or wait for another night?\""
    }
  ],
